Skyline of Santiago City From Santa Lucia Hill, Santiago, Chile

Santiago de Chile is the capital and largest city of Chile. It is also the center of its largest conurbation. Santiago is located in the countrys central valley, at an elevation of 520 m (1, 706 ft) above mean sea level. Santa LucAia Hill is a small hill in the centre of Santiago, Chile. It is situated between Alameda del Libertador Bernardo O Higgins in the south, Santa LucAia Street in the west and Victoria Subercaseaux on the east. The hill has an altitude of 629 m and a height of 69 m over the surrounding area. The hill is the remnant of a volcano 15 million years old. The hill comprises a 65, 300 square metre park adorned with ornate facades, stairways and fountains. Unveiling the Splendour of Australia through Exquisite Artwork. Â© :: Artie | Photography ::
